it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects

Class Object2ShortAVLTreeMap<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObject2ShortFunction<K>
      • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObject2ShortMap<K>
        • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObject2ShortSortedMap<K>
          • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.Object2ShortAVLTreeMap<K>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<K,java.lang.Short>, Object2ShortFunction<K>, Object2ShortMap<K>, Object2ShortSortedMap<K>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,java.lang.Short>, java.util.SortedMap<K,java.lang.Short>

    public class Object2ShortAVLTreeMap<K>
extends AbstractObject2ShortSortedMap<K>
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    A type-specific AVL tree map with a fast, small-footprint implementation.

    The iterators provided by the views of this class are type-specific bidirectional iterators. Moreover, the iterator returned by iterator() can be safely cast to a type-specific list iterator.

        public short addTo(K k,

        Adds an increment to value currently associated with a key.

        Note that this method respects the default return value semantics: when called with a key that does not currently appears in the map, the key will be associated with the default return value plus the given increment.

        Parameters:
        k - the key.
        incr - the increment.
        Returns:
        the old value, or the default return value if no value was present for the given key.
